ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great course, I would definitely recommend to all Computer Science students.
It's a great class that's a lot of fun. I highly recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It showed me that I prefer application work to theoretical work.
This course as very helpful to me as it was my first course in distributed computing, and gave me a good formal theory for the field.

This course was very interesting and helped me to understand better the field of distributed algorithms. Although my research is elsewhere, it has helped me to be more knowledgeable about other CS fields besides my own.
